  <description type="morphology">Shrubs, 40–150 cm. Stems with slender branches from trunks, glabrate, developing fissured barks. Leaves cauline; petioles 2–6 mm; blades green, lanceolate to ovate, 10–25 mm, apices usually acute, sometimes obtuse, faces strigose, gland-dotted. Heads borne singly. Peduncles strigose to glabrate. Involucres 5–11 mm. Phyllaries lanceolate. Ray florets 8–13; corolla laminae 8–12 mm. Disc corollas yellow, 5–6 mm. Cypselae 5–8 mm; pappi 0. 2n = 36.</description>
